<item>
            <title>[LU-111] mount_lustre::parse_options() does not pass force* options down</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-111</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The code look like this:&lt;br/&gt;
                } else if (strncmp(opt, &quot;force&quot;, 5) == 0) {&lt;br/&gt;
                        //XXX special check for &apos;force&apos; option&lt;br/&gt;
                        ++force;&lt;br/&gt;
                        printf(&quot;force: %d\n&quot;, force);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and as a result force* options are not passed down (the likes of force_over_16tb, force_over_8tb and so on).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
